Thanks for all the replies. It happened (again) yesterday, but my
partner was there and she felt uncomfortable, but didn't say anything to the
folks who were talking about the prices to each other. But since it happens
every so often I wondered what you guys would suggest. I usually say that
the item might sit there a long time and leave it at that. The trick comes
when you hope to keep buying from these folks. I have a couple that brings
me things a few at a time....great stuff and I'm anxious to have a crack at
the mother load when they finally move. But I haven't let them see my
previous purchases from them. I have been fair, but there are healthy
mark-ups on these things and I don't want the sweet couple to feel ripped
off. I am lucky...I have two shops so I can &quot;hide&quot; things. But it's a game.
One way we've dealt with this is to stop making offers. They must state
a price and then we go from there. That way it's clear that we aren't
ripping anyone off. If folks insist on us setting a price I'll say &quot;Well,
we'll probably sell that for $100.00 which puts us buying it at $30.00. That
way they are not surprised to see that mark-up. But some folks understand
that business must make profit and some folks just see you taking grannies
stuff.
You not only have to BE honest, you have to LOOK honest.

Tina - I seem to be buying from haunted estates!

